               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370102-name-312" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-312" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-312" type="surname" value="LODER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370102-name-312" type="given" value="CAROLINE"></interp>CAROLINE LODER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Park-place, Mile-end. About eleven o'clock, on the 20th of December, the prisoner came to my house for some shoe ribon which I had not got—I then found him in the shop with this cloak—he had returned from the passage, where the cloak had hung on peg—I charged him with having stolen it—he said he had not—I said it was in his apron—he then dropped it—I went for an officer, and gave him in charge—this is my cloak.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Was it in my apron, or was it on the ground? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Is your apron when I came in.</p>
